WEBVTT

00:06.417 --> 00:08.485
How about "Matt"?

00:08.487 --> 00:09.919
Matt? No.

00:09.921 --> 00:11.488
No, not Matt,
not a shot.

00:11.490 --> 00:12.589
What is wrong
with Matt?

00:12.591 --> 00:13.823
Baby, "Matt"
rhymes with "fat."

00:13.825 --> 00:16.091
He's gonna get made fun of
the first day of pre-K.

00:16.094 --> 00:18.261
And his name has
to have, like...

00:18.263 --> 00:20.163
I don't know,
significance, you know?

00:20.165 --> 00:22.098
Someone that
he can look up to.

00:22.100 --> 00:23.867
Someone like
Jeter.

00:23.869 --> 00:25.869
Very funny.
Come on.

00:25.871 --> 00:27.771
Jeter would be nice.

00:27.773 --> 00:30.006
How about Mike?

00:32.076 --> 00:33.877
Really?
You'd name him...

00:33.879 --> 00:35.178
you'd name him
after me?

00:35.180 --> 00:38.748
Well, you said someone
that he can look up to.

00:38.750 --> 00:40.817
I can't think of a better
role model than you.

00:42.120 --> 00:43.486
You're up, Moses.

00:43.488 --> 00:45.155
What did I do
to deserve you?

00:45.157 --> 00:46.256
Come on, bro.
Nothing.

00:46.258 --> 00:47.490
You got lucky.

00:47.492 --> 00:48.691
Yeah, I got
damn lucky.

00:49.561 --> 00:50.794
Hey!

00:50.796 --> 00:51.795
Hey!

00:55.900 --> 00:57.767
Hey. Baby.

00:57.769 --> 00:58.935
Steph...

00:58.937 --> 01:00.069
Sweetheart.

01:00.071 --> 01:01.471
Hey, can you hear me?

01:01.473 --> 01:02.605
Steph...

01:02.607 --> 01:04.774
Hey, somebody help!

01:04.775 --> 01:06.709
Somebody help us!

01:06.711 --> 01:08.711
Somebody call 911!

01:08.713 --> 01:09.879
Hey.

01:09.881 --> 01:11.181
Somebody help!

01:13.385 --> 01:15.185
Yeah, what's up now?

01:16.488 --> 01:17.887
Got knocked out, right?

01:17.889 --> 01:19.689
Uh, yeah, what's up?

01:24.129 --> 01:25.528
Yeah, I told you,

01:25.530 --> 01:26.830
bro, I'm ready.

01:26.832 --> 01:29.098
Let's see you walk
the dog now, huh?

01:36.407 --> 01:38.374
Tonight's attack
makes three this week

01:38.376 --> 01:40.343
and an even dozen
in the last month.

01:40.345 --> 01:41.344
Pattern?

01:41.346 --> 01:42.545
Chief Helfond?

01:43.515 --> 01:44.514
The incidents are centralized

01:44.516 --> 01:46.816
in Brooklyn and Queens,
mostly at night,

01:46.818 --> 01:49.586
all within a two-block range
of a subway stop.

01:49.588 --> 01:51.087
We're not sure that's a factor,

01:51.089 --> 01:52.889
whether it's a home game
or an away game.

01:52.891 --> 01:55.658
Video surveillance footage
in nearby stations?

01:55.660 --> 01:56.559
Inconclusive.

01:56.561 --> 01:59.329
All right,
so what we know is...?

01:59.331 --> 02:00.763
That this knockout game

02:00.765 --> 02:03.233
is just the kind of
random urban nightmare

02:03.235 --> 02:04.934
that gooses the 11:00 news

02:04.936 --> 02:06.469
and scares the tourists
back to Indiana.

02:06.471 --> 02:07.704
Which is why

02:07.706 --> 02:09.439
the mayor's office is...
We will deal with

02:09.441 --> 02:11.307
the chamber of commerce issues
in due time.

02:11.309 --> 02:12.876
Not our clock to set.

02:16.114 --> 02:17.547
What we know:

02:17.549 --> 02:18.815
it's not
about money;

02:18.817 --> 02:20.450
not one victim was robbed.

02:20.452 --> 02:22.986
Or sex--
there's no sexual assault

02:22.988 --> 02:25.488
attached to any
of the incidents.

02:25.490 --> 02:27.957
Did any of the victims
know their assailants?

02:27.959 --> 02:28.925
Not that we know of.

02:28.927 --> 02:31.594
So it's not revenge, either.

02:34.465 --> 02:37.634
All of the victims are white.

02:37.636 --> 02:39.903
All of the assailants are black.

02:39.905 --> 02:41.070
Yes, so far.

02:41.072 --> 02:42.472
Walks like a hate crime,

02:42.474 --> 02:43.773
talks like a hate crime.

02:46.076 --> 02:47.410
We can call this
whatever we want.

02:47.412 --> 02:49.545
We're going to call it
what it is.

02:49.547 --> 02:50.947
They post the footage

02:50.949 --> 02:52.482
on the Web,

02:52.484 --> 02:53.549
like it's their highlight reel.

02:53.551 --> 02:55.785
So it's also a social
media phenomenon.

02:55.787 --> 02:57.186
So a copycat profile.

02:57.188 --> 02:59.322
In the '80s
we called it "wilding."

02:59.324 --> 03:02.358
Scores of teenagers
rushing through subway cars,

03:02.360 --> 03:03.726
knocking people
to the ground,

03:03.728 --> 03:06.329
snatching whatever
they could get their hands on

03:06.331 --> 03:07.897
like bats out of hell.

03:07.899 --> 03:09.799
Took people years
to get over that.

03:11.436 --> 03:13.169
Where we start:

03:13.171 --> 03:14.871
in the communities,

03:14.873 --> 03:16.839
with our confidential
informants.

03:16.841 --> 03:18.641
What are we offering in return?

03:18.643 --> 03:21.544
Look, this kind of
stupid, random brutality

03:21.546 --> 03:23.579
gives regular street crime
a bad name.

03:23.581 --> 03:25.848
Let's appeal to
the sense of pride

03:25.850 --> 03:27.617
in the professional criminal.

03:27.619 --> 03:28.985
That's all for now.

03:36.627 --> 03:38.528
Could you see their faces,
Mr. Rose?

03:38.530 --> 03:40.163
It was dark.

03:40.165 --> 03:41.164
Okay.

03:41.166 --> 03:43.533
How about, uh, their clothes?

03:43.535 --> 03:44.734
Anything unusual?

03:44.736 --> 03:47.337
Any easily identifiable
pieces of clothing?

03:47.339 --> 03:50.006
No. Do you know how much longer
they're going to be in there?

03:50.008 --> 03:52.241
The doctor said he'd come see us
as soon as he could.

03:52.243 --> 03:54.310
I know, but they've been in there
a long time with her, you know?

03:54.312 --> 03:56.012
I'm sure they're
doing their best.

03:57.881 --> 03:59.549
Could you tell
how tall they were?

03:59.551 --> 04:01.317
Tall, short, average?

04:01.319 --> 04:02.485
Anything?

04:02.487 --> 04:04.587
I don't know.

04:04.589 --> 04:06.856
Was one of them
bigger than the other?

04:06.858 --> 04:09.192
Um... yeah.

04:09.194 --> 04:10.760
Maybe. Honestly, I don't really
remember too much, you know?

04:10.762 --> 04:12.528
Everything happened so fast,
and the three of them

04:12.530 --> 04:13.963
just came out of
nowhere, you know?

04:13.965 --> 04:15.331
Three of them?

04:15.333 --> 04:16.599
You said there were two of them.

04:16.601 --> 04:17.867
Yeah, yeah. No.

04:17.869 --> 04:19.469
Um, I just... I don't know.

04:19.471 --> 04:20.903
Look, I just want
to see Stephanie, you know?

04:20.904 --> 04:22.305
I think... I think
that she needs me,

04:22.307 --> 04:23.506
my baby needs me.

04:23.508 --> 04:24.774
Your wife's pregnant?

04:24.776 --> 04:26.175
Yes.

04:26.177 --> 04:27.443
Our first. Six months.

04:27.445 --> 04:28.444
A little boy.

04:28.446 --> 04:29.445
Mr. Rose?

04:29.447 --> 04:30.747
Yeah, doctor, hey.
How's she doing?

04:30.749 --> 04:31.748
Hey.

04:31.750 --> 04:33.583
Your wife's doing fine.
Okay.

04:33.585 --> 04:34.684
She's stabilized

04:34.686 --> 04:36.452
and is responding
favorably.

04:37.689 --> 04:38.621
Thank God.

04:38.623 --> 04:40.156
Okay, thank you.
Thank you.

04:40.158 --> 04:41.591
And my baby?

04:41.593 --> 04:45.294
Um... maybe you
should have a seat.

